50|$|Ghana's {{first lady}} {{is a member}} of the Ashanti nation. She and her husband have four children, three girls and a boy. When not busy with her family or work, Nana Konadu Agyeman Rawlings enjoys swimming, reading, dancing, camping, and {{collecting}} dolls from around the world. She also devotes time and money to such charitable causes as the National <b>Radiopathy</b> Project, Friends of the National Zoo, and the Ghana Girl Guides Association to name a few.|$|E

